The lower lobe of the right lung was harvested and stored in −80 °C liquid nitrogen. Total RNA was extracted from tissue samples using Trizol reagent. 2 μl of total RNA from each sample in a final reaction volume of 10ul was converted into single-stranded cDNA using SuperScript II Reverse Transcriptase (Invitrogen) following the manufacturer’s recommendations. The RT PCR reaction was carried out with 37 °C for 15 min and 85 °C for 50 s. qRT-PCR was performed using SYBR Premix Taq™ kit with the 95 °C activation step for 30 s; 95 °C denaturation step for 5 s, 62 °C annealing step for 30 s (NF-κB) or 58 °C annealing step for 30 s (TNF-α), 72 °C extension step for 34 s for 40 cycles; and a final extension step of 72 °C for 4 min. The following primers were used: NF-κB forward: 5′-GGG ACT ATG ACT TGA ATG CGG TCC -3′, reverse: 5′-CAG GTC CCG TGA AAT ACA CCT CAA-3′; TNF-α forward: 5′-CTT CTG TCT ACT GAA CTT CGG-3′, reverse: 5′-GTG CTT GAT CTG TTG TTT CC-3′; GAPDH forward: 5′-ACC ACA GTC CAT GCC ATC AC-3′, reverse: 5′-TCC ACC ACC CTG TTG CTG TA-3′. Results in triplicate were expressed as relative transcriptions of the NF-κB mRNA and TNF-α mRNA using the following formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
